<DOC><DOCNO> AP900706-0193 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-07-06-90 2334EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r a AM-SniperKilling     07-06 0172</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Sniper Killing,0178</SECOND><HEAD>One Killed In Sniper Ambush</HEAD><DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A sniper fired into a crowd near a bar Friday,killing a teen-ager and wounding three other people, police said.   ``It was like an ambush,'' said police Lt. William Mullen.``Apparently, the shots were fired randomly from a distance. Thevictims didn't really know where the shots were coming from.''   Police made no arrests.   Killed was Shon Staton, 17, of McKeesport. The three others whowere struck by gunfire weren't seriously hurt, police said.   The sniper fired several rifle shots from woods into the crowdoutside the bar around 2:30 a.m., Mullen said.   Members of the crowd told police they heard three to seven shots.   Staton died about 40 minutes later at Forbes Metropolitan HealthCenter, the Allegheny County Coroner's Office said.   Police said the shooting came 15 minutes after a man attacked awoman about a half block from the bar, then returned with a rifleand threatened to kill her. The man then left without incident,police said.</TEXT></DOC>